7 An Act relating to aeronautics; identifying original
appropriation; transferring remaining funds to the
8 Long-Term Aerospace and Aeronautics Infrastructure
Sustainability Revolving Fund; providing for
9 noncodification; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
14 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
15 Of the Fifty-seven Million Dollars ($57,000,000.00) appropriated
16 to the Oklahoma Department of Aerospace and Aeronautics in Section
17 72 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1125 of the 2nd Session of the 59th
18 Oklahoma Legislature, Forty-one Million Dollars ($41,000,000.00) or
19 so much as may be necessary shall be transferred to the Long-Term
20 Aerospace and Aeronautics Infrastructure Sustainability Revolving
21 Fund created in Section 415 of Title 3 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
